              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:δαιμόνιον&lt;SDBG:δαιμόνιον:000000&gt;}[a] ‘demon,’ {D:12.37}) to be possessed by a demon</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be demon possessed</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages one cannot speak of a person ‘being possessed by a demon.’ A more appropriate expression may be ‘the person possesses a demon.’ In other instances an idiomatic phrase is employed, ‘the demon rides the person’ or ‘the demon commands the person’ or even ‘the demon is the person.’</Comments>
